article.headline: Troy 56, Fla. International 51
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Troy's Cedric Jackson led all scorers with 20 points in the team's 56-51 win at Florida International on Thursday night. Jackson hit a 3-point basket with 2:38 to play that gave Troy the lead for good. Alex Galindo was Florida International's top scorer with 14 points. Florida International (9-14, 4-9 Sun Belt Conference) led 30-28 at the half and clung to that advantage throughout most of the second half. The Golden Panthers grabbed their biggest lead of the game, 35-28, on a Chris Fuller jumper two minutes into the second half. But the Trojans (11-14, 6-8), who were held nearly 18 points below their season scoring average, stayed close and then turned up their own defensive effort. Florida International led 46-41 with 8:28 to play when Troy went on a 6-0 run over the next two minutes to take its first lead of the second half, 47-46. A jumper from Johwen Villegas put the Golden Panthers up 48-47 with 3:54. But the Trojans countered with Jackson's 3-pointer keying a 7-1 run over the next 3:32, ensuring Troy's victory.
